      "content": "There is no perfect balance because the current federal minimum wage is a one-size-fits-all mandate that ignores the stark economic differences between a major city and a small Midwest town. While some businesses might survive by raising prices, many will inevitably face closures or forced layoffs, creating a net loss for the local community. The only real solution lies in state-level incentives or tax breaks specifically designed to offset these costs, rather than waiting for a federal compromise that rarely benefits the struggling small business owner.",
